verbose_text: Humans who experience subjective social isolation are known to have higher expression of IGFBP3 from peripheral sampling (leukocytes) XREF_BIBR and while it is difficult to compare across tissue samples it could be that the elevated IGFBP3 reported by XREF_BIBR may be an effect of social isolation, as in the above human study, and not a result of up-regulation after play behaviour.
